videos.description: Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney proud to have team play in ACC Championship
videos.headline: Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney proud to have team play in ACC Championship

videos.description: Clemson takes the opening possession and goes 75 yards in nine plays, ending with Deshaun Watson going up the middle for the end zone putting the Tigers up early 7-0.
videos.headline: Clemson caps opening driving with Watson's 3-yard TD

videos.description: Deshaun Watson runs the option to perfection keeping the ball before finding Jordan Leggett wide open over the middle for a 21-yard touchdown to increase Clemson's lead to 14-0.
videos.headline: Clemson strikes again with 21-yard TD to Leggett

videos.description: Jerod Evans pass complete to Sam Rogers for a loss of 1 yard to the VTech 22 for a 1ST down CLEMSON Penalty, Personal Foul (Dorian O'Daniel) to the VTech 37 for a 1ST down
videos.headline: Clemson's O'Daniel ejected for targeting

videos.description: Mitchell Ludwig pass complete to Terrell Edmunds for 20 yds to the Clem 42 for a 1ST down
videos.headline: Virginia Tech converts on fake punt after review

videos.description: After spotting Clemson an early 14 point lead, Virginia Tech finally answers when Travon McMillian punches it in from a yard out to cut the deficit to 14-7.
videos.headline: McMillian punches it in to get Virginia Tech on the board

videos.description: Clemson has yet to be stopped on offense making it three touchdowns in three possessions when Deshaun Watson finds Jordan Leggett in the end zone for a second time to put the Tigers up 21-7.
videos.headline: Watson to Leggett combo works again

videos.description: Jerod Evans pass complete to Isaiah Ford for 53 yds to the Clem 17 for a 1ST down
videos.headline: J. Evans pass to I. Ford for 53 yds for a 1ST down

videos.description: Jerod Evens won't be denied as he busts through a number of Clemson tackles to find the end zone and bring Virginia Tech back to within seven.
videos.headline: Evans busts tackles for the goal line and a Virginia Tech TD

videos.description: Deshaun Watson is putting on a show for the Heisman voters as he accounts for a trio of touchdowns in the first half of the ACC championship game.
videos.headline: Watson starring for Clemson with three first-half TDs

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Watson three TDs in first half) 2016/12/3 ESHEET

videos.description: Virginia Tech head coach Justin Fuente pleased with team's performance in 1st half
videos.headline: Virginia Tech head coach Justin Fuente pleased with team's performance in 1st half

videos.description: Deshaun Watson pass intercepted Andrew Motuapuaka return for no gain to the Clem 38
videos.headline: Tipped pass leads to interception for Virginia Tech

videos.description: Wayne Gallman slaloms through the defense to pay dirt capping an 89-yard drive with an 8-yard touchdown to put Clemson up 28-14.
videos.headline: Gallman gets in the end zone for Clemson TD

videos.description: Jerod Evans pass intercepted Cordrea Tankersley return for no gain to the Clem 49
videos.headline: J. Evans pass intercepted by C. Tankersley

videos.description: Deshaun Watson appears to get stuffed short of the goal line until he gets some help from his friends on the offensive line to push him into the end zone for another Clemson touchdown.
videos.headline: Watson gets some help to score again for Clemson

videos.description: Travon McMillian run for 27 yds for a TD
videos.headline: T. McMillian run for 27 yds for a TD

videos.description: Virginia Tech refuses to go away, scoring 14 unanswered points to cut Clemson's lead to 35-28 after Jerod Evans busts his way into the end zone from five yards out.
videos.headline: Evans barrels his way in for Virginia Tech TD

videos.description: Deshaun Watson rolls out and hits Hunter Renfrow on the sideline who scampers 15 yards to the end zone giving Clemson back its 14 point lead in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Clemson regains cushion with 15-yard Renfrow TD

videos.description: Jerod Evans finds Cam Philips streaking behind the defense for a 26-yard touchdown to bring Virginia Tech back to within 7 points again.
videos.headline: Evans hits Philips to keep Virginia Tech hanging around

videos.description: Jerod Evans pass intercepted Cordrea Tankersley return for no gain to the Clem 15
videos.headline: Tankersley picks off Evans again to seal ACC title for Clemson

videos.description: Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney discusses victory over Virginia Tech in ACC Championship
videos.headline: Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney discusses victory over Virginia Tech in ACC Championship

videos.description: Clemson quarterback Deshaun Watson breaks down teammates' performance in win over Virginia Tech
videos.headline: Clemson quarterback Deshaun Watson breaks down teammates' performance in win over Virginia Tech

videos.description: Virginia Tech didn't make it easy, but Clemson was able to hold off the Hokies' late rally to win their second straight ACC championship with a 42-35 victory.
videos.headline: Clemson holds on for second straight ACC title
